
-------------- MAC -------------------

######### IOS ###########
1. Install Xcode - get it for free from App Store
   -> it will ask you to accept licence in terminal, just follow instruction and type accept

2. ionic cordova emulate ios --livereload

######### ANDROID ###########
1. Download and install android studtio

2. We need to install gradle - (gradle is system to help you build your code for emulator)

3. brew install gradle
    -> if you don't have homebrew go to official website https://brew.sh/ and copy command for installation

4. Run you Android studio and create empty project in order to install all of the, updates, SDKs and packages.

5. Create new virtual device in tools/VD

6. All done (:

7. ionic cordova emulate android --livereload

-------------- WINDOWS -------------------

######### IOS ###########
1. Cannot run because Xcode is not available for windows :(

######### ANDROID ###########
1. Download and install android studtio

2. Download latest gradle binary - https://gradle.org/releases/

3. Create a new directory C:\Gradle with File Explorer. -> or directory of your choice

4. Unpack your downloaded gradle binary to C:\Gradle

5. In File Explorer right-click on the This PC (or Computer) icon, then click Properties -> Advanced System Settings -> Environmental Variables.

6. Under System Variables select Path, then click Edit. Add an entry for C:\Gradle\gradle-4.9\bin. Click OK to save.
  -> Image Tutorial: https://www.computerhope.com/issues/ch000549.htm

7. Open a console (or a Windows command prompt) and run gradle -v to run gradle and display the version, e.g.:

8. Run you Android studio and create empty project in order to install all of the, updates, SDKs and packages.

9. Create new virtual device in tools/VD

10. All done (:

11. ionic cordova emulate android --livereload

